<HEADLINE>
FT  11 AUG 93 / Letter: Vocational training debate needs answers
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   From Mr RODNEY J COPPING
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir, Your leader item, 'Leaving school' (August 10), reiterates the
never-ending debate without resolution on vocational training.
The plethora of reviews and reports has failed miserably in identifying a
basic requirement. There is a fundamental need to make business and
education interface directly, perhaps statutorily, and with consistent joint
funding.
The current fragmented and piecemeal initiatives, hyped by lip service and
inadequately funded, will leave vocational training as it has been regarded
for a hundred years - an activity for the underprivileged.
Educationalists and industrialists should stop debating where responsibility
lies and jointly commit substantial resources to a long-term strategy for
educating and training our future workforce.
Rodney J Copping,
director,
Qualitair Training Services,
Tudor Grange,
Blossomfield Road,
Solihull,
West Midlands B91 1SA
</TEXT>
