<HEADLINE>
FT  11 AUG 93 / People: Owners Abroad
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Owners Abroad yesterday confirmed that Michael Julien, 55, former chief
executive of Storehouse is to become non-executive chairman from the
beginning of September.
Last month, the holiday company said that group profits this year are likely
to be half market expectations. While successfully fighting off a takeover
bid from rival Airtours, Owners Abroad had given the impression that its
prospects were rosy. Although the group insists the market deteriorated
after the bid battle had ended, chairman Howard Klein announced his
resignation in July.
Prior to Storehouse, Julien was successively finance director of BICC,
Midland Bank and Guinness.
