FT  11 AUG 93 / Hospital waiting lists top 1 million
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE NUMBER of people on hospital waiting lists has topped a million for the
first time.
Provisional Department of Health statistics published yesterday show 22,789
people joined waiting lists in the three months to the end of June, when the
total reached 1,017,763. Over that period hospital waiting lists of people
waiting more than a year for treatment grew by 15.7 per cent to 65,465.
But Dr Brian Mawhinney, health minister, said the figures showed the number
of patients waiting more than a year for treatment was down by 17,000
compared with the same period last year.
