<TEXT>
FOKKER, the Dutch aircraft maker majority-owned by Deutsche Aerospace (Dasa)
of Germany, reported a net loss of Fl 127m (Dollars 65m) for the first half
of 1993 and reaffirmed earlier forecasts of a full-year loss of around Fl
150m.
