a reduction in aircraft output.
Turnover fell by 8 per cent to Fl 1.73bn and operating profit before
interest expenses to Fl 55.1m from Fl 62.8m.
The company said that recent orders received for its 100-seat Fokker 100
were a first sign that parts of the depressed aircraft market was starting
to recover.
