FT  10 AUG 93 / UK Company News: Receivers called in at Dunkeld
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Dunkeld, the shirt and swimwear manufacturer, went into receivership
yesterday. The group's banks were not prepared to refinance the company
which was facing a liquidity crisis. Its shares had been suspended at 28p on
Friday.
In February, the group returned annual pre-tax profits of Pounds 2.45m,
against a loss of Pounds 17.5m. Dunkeld has debt of about Pounds 7m, the
legacy of rapid expansion in the 1980s.
