<HEADLINE>
FT  10 AUG 93 / UK Company News: MTM cuts deficit to Pounds 11.9m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CATHERINE MILTON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
MTM, the chemicals company which in April sold most of its assets to reduce
debt, yesterday announced a reduction in losses from Pounds 28m to Pounds
11.9m pre-tax in the six months to end-June.
The deficit bore exceptional charges of Pounds 9.64m (Pounds 9.34m).
MTM has been reorganised under a reshuffled board since its shares collapsed
last year when a Serious Fraud Office enquiry was launched hard on the heels
of the company making two profit warnings in March 1992.
Mr David Swallow, the new chairman, said the company, which has Pounds 10.8m
in cash after the Pounds 100m sale of assets to rivals BTP, planned to
invest in new categories of 'science-based' businesses.
He said: 'The figures have limited relevance to the company's on-going
position with the exception of MTM Agrochemicals which remains within the
group.'
Turnover of Pounds 46.4m (Pounds 56.5m) included Pounds 32.5m (Pounds 45m)
from discontinued operations. Turnover on continuing operations - MTM
Agrochemicals - rose to Pounds 13.8m (Pounds 11.5m).
That business contributed an operating profit of Pounds 296,000 compared
with losses of Pounds 10.3m in the previous period, which reflected
provisions for permanent diminution in assets following a revaluation.
Mr Swallow said that seasonal fluctuations in demand for MTM Agrochemicals
meant the second half would not match the first: 'However, the board
continues to expect the business to break even for the year as a whole.'
Total operating profits were Pounds 1.51m (loss of Pounds 9.45m).
The Pounds 9.64m exceptional charge represented a Pounds 31.3m loss on
disposal of discontinued operations, including Pounds 25.4m of goodwill
previously written off, partly offset by a Pounds 21.7m provision made in
1992.
Net interest payments were Pounds 3.77m (Pounds 4.78m). Losses per share
emerged at 60.6p, down from 157p.
Following a Pounds 28.9m debt into equity swap, net liabilities of Pounds
23.5m in the December 31 balance sheet had become net assets of Pounds 20m,
or 77p per share, by the half-way stage.
There is again no interim dividend.
</TEXT>
