FT  10 AUG 93 / World Stock Markets: South Africa
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
BULLION price recovery hopes and the weak financial rand took gold shares
higher, the sector index rising 52 to 1,866, and industrials were lifted in
aggregate by the news that the conglomerate, Barlow Rand, would announce its
unbundling strategy after hours. Industrials rose 20 to 4,580 and the
