FT  10 AUG 93 / Letter: A better way to save on energy bills
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   From Mr GEOFF STEPHENSON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir, Re 'Advance payments could avoid VAT on fuel bills' (August 7), if
energy consumers have cash to spare for such payments they would be far
better advised to spend it on energy efficiency improvements at home - thus
saving themselves far more than the 8 per cent VAT this year, next year, and
for ever more.
An investment of Pounds 1,500 in the right combination of house insulation,
draught proofing, heating controls, low energy lighting and a more efficient
boiler could save a typical householder 30-50 per cent of their energy bills
 -enough to pay the VAT and still have change.
And if all the energy and hot air devoted by populist politicians in
attacking VAT on fuel had been devoted to the cause of energy efficiency,
we'd all be better off, with lower fuel bills and less environmental damage.
Geoff Stephenson,
Chalk Line,
12 Pond Close,
Harefield,
Middlesex UB9 6NG
