<HEADLINE>
FT  10 AUG 93 / Dutch bargemen back at work
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RONALD VAN DE KROL
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   AMSTERDAM
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Striking Dutch bargemen returned to work yesterday after a six-week
stoppage, but said they may resume their actions in three months if a
dispute over cargo allocation is not settled, writes Ronald van de Krol in
Amsterdam.
The independent barge owner-operators have been blocking some river traffic
and refusing to take cargoes since June to press their demands that
'tourderole', a traditional cargo allocation system for shipments from the
Netherlands to Belgium, be written into Dutch law.
